The paper deals with nonexistence results of generalized bent functions, which are related to cryptography and coding theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also involves algebraic and number theoretic concepts, which suggest that it could be submitted to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from discrete mathematics and combinatorics, which could make it relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
